  <div class="row" id="dashboard">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
      <div class="card card-user">
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">
          </p>
          <div class="author">
            <div class="block block-one"></div>
            <div class="block block-two"></div>
            <div class="block block-three"></div>
            <div class="block block-four"></div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0)">
              <h3 class="title">Dashboard</h3>
            </a>
            <p class="description">
              What is the Dashboard page?
            </p>
          </div>
          <p></p>
          <div class="card-description">
            <p>
              The dashboard page exists to report information about Theta and Tfuel price evolution, as well as some
              information about a wallet.<br>
              To get information about a specific wallet, it possible to either search for it
              by address or <a href="#domain">domain</a> by clicking on the search bar,
              or connect your wallet using the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
              Theta Wallet extension.</a><br>
              It currently has 5 widgets:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><b>Tfuel/Theta line chart: </b> This widget provide historic price information for both crypto
                currencies. It can be filtered by year, month or week
              </li>
              <li><b> Wallet Composition: </b> It display a pie chart, representing all the Theta and Tfuel held by
                the wallet with the
                composition in $ value.
              </li>
              <li><b> Theta and Tfuel price: </b> Theses two widgets gives live information about the current price,
                the delta with the last 24hours, and delta with the last 7 days, as well as market cap.
              </li>
              <li><b> Guardian Node Reward Forecast: </b> Staking Theta on a Guardian Node gives TFuel as rewards. There
                is a minimum of {{format-number 1000}} Theta requirement in order to stake. This widget take an input of
                amount of Theta and
                forecast how many Tfuel will be rewarded by day/month/year.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
