  <div class="row" id="domain">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
      <div class="card card-user">
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">
          </p>
          <div class="author">
            <div class="block block-one"></div>
            <div class="block block-two"></div>
            <div class="block block-three"></div>
            <div class="block block-four"></div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0)">
              <h3 class="title">Domain</h3>
            </a>
            <p class="description">
              What is a Domain?
            </p>
          </div>
          <p></p>
          <div class="card-description">
            <p>
              Domains are a way of associating a wallet address with a domain name on the Theta blockchain. <br>
              They remove the need for copying and pasting long addresses. You can use them to easily explore a wallet
              or send Tfuels to someone. <br>
              Domains are using a public smart contract that can be found on
              <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/thetaboard-org/smart_contracts/blob/master/contracts/addressName.sol">
                github </a><br>
              <br>
              To buy a new domain, you will need to be on chrome and use the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
              Theta Wallet extension.</a><br>
            </p>
            <br>
            <h4>Buy a Theta Domain Name</h4>
            <p>
              Search for a domain on the
              <LinkTo @route="domain"> domain page</LinkTo>
              , and see if it is available or not. <br>
              If available the domain can be bought for 5 Tfuel buy clicking on the "Review Order" button. It will
              open a popup on the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
              Theta Wallet extension</a> to confirm the transaction.
              If a domain is already used by someone, an offer can be made for at least 1 Tfuel to the current owner of
              the domain.<br>
              Once a offered as been entered, clicking the "Review Order" button will
              open a popup on the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
              Theta Wallet extension</a>. Which will lock the funds for the offer on the smart contract<br>
              The offer can be canceled at any time, and the smart contract will send all the Tfuels back to the wallet.<br>
              The owner of the domain can either accept or reject the offer.
            </p>
            <br>
            <h4>Address lookup</h4>
            <p> An address can be entered on the Address lookup, it will return all the domains associated with it.
              The button "My domain name" can be clicked on to link your wallet using the <a
                      target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
                Chrome extension</a>.
            </p>
            <br>
            <h4>My offers</h4>
            <p> The state of offers can be seen in this widget. The offers made by the current connected wallet, can be
              canceled at any time. Which will transfer the Tfuels from the smart contract to the wallet which made the
              offer.<br>
              Accepting an offer can be done by clicking on the "accept offer" button.
              Which will open a confirmation popup on the wallet. Once confirmed, the smart contract will send the
              90% of the Tfuels to the wallet that accepted the offer, 10% to Thetaboard.io support,
              and transfer ownership of the domain to the new owner. <br>
              If not satisfied with an offer, it is possible to reject it by clicking on the "reject offer" button.
              The smart contract will send back the Tfuels to the wallet that made the offer. Once the rejection is
              confirm.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row" id="guardian">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
      <div class="card card-user">
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">
          </p>
          <div class="author">
            <div class="block block-one"></div>
