              <h3 class="title">Guardian Node</h3>
            </a>
            <p class="description">
              What is the Guardian Node page?
            </p>
          </div>
          <p></p>
          <div class="card-description">
            <p>
              Guardian Node have an important part of the Theta, they form a second layer defense against potential
              malicious attackers on the blockchain. <br>
              Staking a minimum of {{format-number 1000}} Theta on a a guardian node will reward proportionally in
              Tfuels.Forecasting can be found on the dashboard.<br>
              Staking Theta on a Guardian Node will keep the Theta on the wallet. The Guardian Node will NOT be in
              control of the Theta, it is always possible to withdraw them.
            </p><br>
            <h4> Using Thetaboard public Guardian Node</h4>
            <p>
              Thetaboard.io host a public Guardian Node for the community. Anyone can use it by either using summary on
              the page and the <a target="_blank" href="https://docs.thetatoken.org/docs/guardian-staking-process">Theta
              instructions</a>.<br>
              Or the Stake widget can be used. Clicking on the "Deposit" button will ask for an amount of Theta, then
              clicking on "Review Deposit", will open a confirmation on the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
              Theta Wallet extension.</a> <br> <br>
              Unstacking Theta can be done at any time by either using the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://docs.thetatoken.org/docs/withdrawing-your-stake-from-the-guardian-node">Theta
              documentation</a> or by clicking on the "Withdraw" button
            </p><br>
            <h4>Summary and Logs</h4>
            <p>
              The Guardian Node Address and Summary are displayed. It is possible to click on it to copy the
              content.<br>
              Curious people can click on the "Guardian Logs" icon, to get the latest logs from the running Guardian
              Node.
            </p>
            <h4> Hosting a Guardian Node</h4>
            <p>
              For more advanced users it is possible to setup a Guardian Node using the using the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://docs.thetatoken.org/docs/guardian-node-overview">Theta documentation</a><br>
              Or by setting up an instance of Thetaboard. Which can be done by running the following commands on a linux
              terminal: <br>
              <code>
                curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/momohuri/thetaboard/main/Makefile -o ./Makefile <br>
                NODE_PASSWORD='A-SECRET-PASSWRD' make start_thetaboard<br>
              </code>
              <br>
              Mode information can be found on our <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://github.com/momohuri/thetaboard">github</a>.<br>

              Setting up a custom Guardian Node unlock features to start/stop the guardian Node, update to the latest
              binaries, and download the latest snapshot.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
